The story revolves around "Mob," a boy who will explode if his emotional capacity reaches 100%. This boy with psychic powers earned his nickname "Mob" because he does not stand out among other people. He keeps his psychic powers bottled up so he can live normally, but if his emotional level reaches 100, something will overwhelm his entire body.
(Source: Anime News Network)

The suspense horror/dark fantasy story is set in Tokyo, which is haunted by mysterious "ghouls" who are devouring humans. People are gripped by the fear of these ghouls whose identities are masked in mystery. An ordinary college student named Kaneki encounters Rize, a girl who is an avid reader like him, at the caf he frequents. Little does he realize that his fate will change overnight.
(Source: Anime News Network)

Young Asta was born with no magic ability in a world where magic is everything. In order to prove his strength and keep a promise with his friend, Asta dreams of becoming the greatest mage in the land, the Wizard King!
(Source: Viz Media)

Meet the would-be assassins of class 3-E: Sugino, who let his grades slip and got kicked off the baseball team. Karma, whos doing well in his classes but keeps getting suspended for fighting. And Okuda, who lacks both academic and social skills, yet excels at one subject: chemistry. Who has the best chance of winning that reward? Will the deed be accomplished through pity, brute force or poison...? And what chance does their teacher have of repairing his students tattered self-esteem? (Source: Viz Media) Included Extra Chapters: Volume 1: Koro Sensei's Drawing Song Volume 2: Koro Sensei vs. Kusuo Saiki, Iruma City Battle Volume 7: Koro Sensei vs. Kusuo Saiki, Iruma City Battle II Volume 21: Time to Come Home Volume 21: Time to go to the Izakaya Volume 21: Time to Reveal Identities Volume 21: Time to Say Thank You Volume 21: Tokyo Department Store War Journal
